review_text: When I walked into this location the other day with a few savings bonds and not being a customer with this brand due to the highest fees in the region, I was surprised by the cleanliness and quality this bank gave to me to get the transaction done correctly.  They were very organized, and the waiting area felt way too spacious enough.  I felt like I was a "King" to the amount of space this bank held. I actually felt I could actually "breathe" again-something my choice in banks doesn't even feel they should give the customer/me yet. It was so good, I can actually comment on how clean the floor was, that I can say I could physically see my face from the fully-vacuumed carpeting at this location.

The M and T bank has the worst customer service I have ever encountered.  The manager Dave (heavy set guy), refused to speak with me on the phone to validate a certified check.  He treated me like I had leprosy!  I'll never bank with them again.
